<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4634162>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Herdmania grandis (A, C, D, F, QM GH377; B, E, QM GH2200; G, QM GH5759): A, body from left side showing muscles; B, dorsal tubercle showing early stage in development of convoluted slit; C, portion of dorsal lamina; D, gut loop; E, F, anus and gonoducal openings; G, anus. Scale bars: A, D = 5.0 mm; B, E-G = 1.0mm; C = 0.5mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4634162/files/figure.png" .

